<h2>Position Summary:</h2>

We are seeking an individual with culinary or restaurant experience to assume the role of Food and Beverage Director for our hospitality based senior living community. This person will be responsible for managing and coordinating all the daily functions within the department as well as the staff members. This position includes monitoring the services of food and drinks, as well as knowledge of labor laws and health compliance regulations. 

WESTliving is looking to fill this position with a person who possesses the following talents:

<strong>Service</strong> - A drive to be of service to others
<strong>Discipline</strong> - A need to impose structure into life and work
<strong>Individualized Perception</strong> - An awareness of and attentiveness to individual differences
<strong>Developer</strong> - A need to invest in others and to derive satisfaction in doing so
<strong>Command</strong> - An ability to take charge

In addition to the talents listed above WESTliving is looking to fill this position with a person who possesses the following:

<h3>Skills</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Able to instruct as well as listen. Effectively understands, deciphers and relates WESTlivingâ€™s vision to employees</li>
    <li>Knowledge of principles and processes for providing customer and personal services. This includes customer needs assessment, meeting quality standards for services, and evaluation of customer satisfaction</li>
    <li>Knowledge of principles and methods for curriculum and training design as well as the ability to teach and instruct individuals</li>
    <li>Knowledge of raw materials, production processes, quality control, costs, and other techniques for maximizing effective manufacturing and distribution of goods</li>
    <li>Ability to cook and prepare food in accordance with culinary program</li>
</ul>

<h3>Knowledge</h3>
<ul>
    <li>3 years Culinary and Chef experience, Front of the House experience desirable</li>
    <li>Minimum 3 years of experience, 1 year in a supervisory role</li>
    <li>Restaurant/hotel experience preferred</li>
    <li>Experience with special diets, scratch cooking, baking, catering, and volume cooking</li> 
    <li>Menu planning experience required</li>
    <li>ServSafe Certification required</li>
</ul>

<h3>About us</h3>
WESTliving was formed in early 2009 to own and operate hospitality based senior living communities. Our communities provide a variety of lifestyles, wellness, and care options. We are uncompromising in our commitment to quality and service excellence. WESTlivingâ€™s culture is grounded in the fact that daily actions and behaviors support our shared vision to be the most respected and recognized service company in the world.

The WESTclass Team of talented and experienced leaders in the industry bring a customer centered approach to senior living. Team members are driven by WESTliving Core Values, Mission, and Service Standards as guiding principles to be engaged, responsible and attentive to all we serve in achieving our Vision.

<h3>Join our Team!</h3>
